			array(
				'judul' => 'ANTAM Synergize with Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources & SOEs Cares for Emergency Response Semeru in Lumajang',
				'deskripsi' => '<p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Jakarta, December 7, 2021</span>&nbsp;-&nbsp; PT Aneka Tambang Tbk (ANTAM; IDX: ANTM; ASX: ATM), a member of MIND ID - BUMN Holding Mining Industry, synergize with a joint Emergency Response Group (ERG) under the coordination of the Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources and the Ministry of State-Owned Enterprises (SOE’s) participated in accelerating humanitarian assistance to communities affected by the natural disaster of Mount Semeru\'s eruption in Lumajang Regency, East Java.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">ANTAM\'s Corporate Secretary, Mr. Yulan Kustiyan said that the Company also supports the Government\'s emergency response to the Mount Semeru eruption.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">“Some of the activities that have been carried out include coordination, establishment of Command Posts, search for victims and evacuation, as well as joint evaluations with related institution and local office. We will also provide logistical assistance such as staple foods, blankets and toddler/baby food,” said Yulan.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">Yulan hopes that with ANTAM\'s support in this effort, it can ease the burden of the victims in Lumajang residents which have been hit by this disaster.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">“Hopefully the condition of the victims in the affected areas will improve soon. We together with the Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources Team &amp; SOE’s Cares will do our best to help the disaster management process,” he added.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">ANTAM\'s ERG team, which are members of the Ministry of Energy and Mineral Resources Team &amp; SOE’s Cares, arrived at the affected location since last Monday, December 6 2021 by sending 10 (ten) people consisting of several Companies which were divided into rescuers, medical and evacuation personnel.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">The field coordinators in charge are General Coordinator: Mr. Asril (ANTAM); Logistics Coordinator: Mining Inspector (KESDM); Rescue Coordinator 1: Mr. Sugeng H (PT Bank Syariah Indonesia); Rescue Coordinator 2: Mr. Syahroni (PT Perusahaan Pengelola Asset); and Health Coordinator: Mr. Nasir (PT Paiton Energy).</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">Before moving to the affected areas in Koboan Curah Hamlet and Kajar Kuning Hamlet, Pronojiwo District, Lumajang Regency, the team also coordinated with the National Search and Rescue Agency (Basarnas), the Regional Disaster Management Agency (BPBD) of Lumajang Regency, the TNI and POLRI.<br style="display: block;">In this initial stage, the team has established the Command Post and continues to search for residents and evacuate residents to the evacuation post.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">Today, the joint team also carried out health checks and treatment for the refugees at the Tumpeng Village Head Office, Candipuro District, Lumajang Regency.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">“ANTAM together with the joint team will synergize with related parties to accelerate the handling of the Semeru emergency response in Lumajang,” concluded Yulan.</p>',
				'author' => 'Admin',
				'category' => 'News',
				'slug' => 'antam-synergize-with-ministry-of-energy-and-mineral-resources-soes-cares-for-emergency-response-semeru-in-lumajang',
				'img' => '/images/article/1639631933_61b0015257240-20211208075026-2.jpg',
				'created_at' => '2021-12-15 21:18:53',
				'updated_at' => '2021-12-15 21:18:53',
			),
			2 =>
			array(
				'judul' => 'ANTAM Assists Renovation of the West Kalimantan Province Manpower Certification Center',
				'deskripsi' => '<p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;"><span style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: 700; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">Pontianak, December 6, 2021</span>&nbsp;- PT Aneka Tambang Tbk (ANTAM; IDX: ANTM; ASX: ATM) member of Mining Industry Indonesia (MIND ID) - the State-Owned Enterprise Holding of the Mining Industry, with the Provincial Government of West Kalimantan signed a Memorandum of Understanding for the Renovation and Procurement of Mechanic Workshop Equipment in West Kalimantan Province Manpower Certification Center.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">The agreement to improve human resources in West Kalimantan was signed by West Kalimantan Governor, Mr. Sutarmidji and ANTAM\'s Human Resources Director, Mr. Luki Setiawan Suardi on Tuesday, November 30, 2021 in Pontianak.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">ANTAM\'s Corporate Secretary, Mr. Yulan Kustiyan, said that the commitment to assist in the renovation and procurement of mechanical workshop equipment for the West Kalimantan Manpower Certification Center is the Company\'s responsibility to increase human resources around the operational area.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">“This is a manifestation of the implementation of ANTAM\'s Pillars, namely Superior Synergy and Powerful Synergy. We continue to be committed to improving the competence and skills of the community around the Company\'s operational areas,” said Yulan.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">Yulan hopes that ANTAM\'s support in building renovations and equipment procurement at the West Kalimantan Manpower Certification Center can help the community in getting job opportunities.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">“Hopefully, this assistance can also make the West Kalimantan people able to compete because they have the necessary skills and increase economic value for the community, in line with the Pillars of Powerful Synergy and Economic Synergy,” he added.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">Meanwhile, West Kalimantan Governor Sutarmidji expressed his appreciation for ANTAM\'s assistance. “We express our gratitude for ANTAM\'s collaboration in developing human resources in West Kalimantan. Currently, the condition of the mechanical workshop is not feasible. With the assistance provided by ANTAM, We hope we can improve the condition of the workshop,” he said.</p><p style="margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.667em; font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); text-align: justify; margin-top: 0.6rem !important; margin-bottom: 0.6rem !important;">He added that the West Kalimantan Provincial Government intends to turn the training center into an integrated certification center. “We will use the assistance provided by ANTAM to build the needed facilities and infrastructure. We also open up opportunities for ANTAM to be able to use the certification center for employee training at a cost from the West Kalimantan Provincial Government through the Office of Manpower and Transmigration (Disnakertrans),” he concluded.</p>',
				'author' => 'Admin',
				'category' => 'News',
				'slug' => 'antam-assists-renovation-of-the-west-kalimantan-province-manpower-certification-center',
				'img' => '/images/article/1639632027_61add24bb32c9-20211206160515-2-1.jpg',
				'created_at' => '2021-12-15 21:20:27',
				'updated_at' => '2021-12-15 21:20:27',
			),
			3 =>
